</p></section><section id="GUID-D6A320CB-A65B-4F37-95BD-F90DE7BDD45D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">When the patterns of the NozzleJet variation are can't be measured correctly, this warning is generated. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In most cases a visual inspection of the printed test-chart can already point towards the root cause of the failed measurement. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Specific areas to look for are the shape of the markers and the uniformity of the bars. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Failing nozzles or incorrect media steps are in most cases the cause of this warning.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-480B4E14-7AB9-4230-BBE2-97A999EC3E19.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
